verbose_text: EROBI and EROMI must have declined in the prealpine regions where livestock production gained in relative importance, and increased in regions where forests or cropping became more dominant, i.e. in the mountainous regions where considerable reforestation occurred, as well as in the crop producing regions in the Eastern part of the Danube Basin.2 (2) As compared to Spain, Austrian " Final EROI " (final produce divided by total inputs consumed) was higher throughout the 20th century.
